  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWe use `slog` to log to CLI for both the `beacon_node` and `validator_client`.\r\n\r\nIt's working well but we also need the option to log to file so we can examine the logs later.\r\n\r\nI think the best UX would be adding a CLI flag that allows setting the debug level for the log file, then dumping into some JSON file.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n1. Figure out if there's some established flag by geth/parity for logging to file. If so, use that.\r\n1. See if there's some standard \"logging\" directory accessible in `std::path` (or w/e). If so, use that. Alternatively, add another flag to specify where the logs should go with a sensible default -- probably in the `~/.lighthouse` dir.(If there's some Eth1.x standard here, go for it).\r\n1. Figure out how to make `slog` dump to JSON.\r\n\r\nFYI, all the CLI flags and `slog` init code is [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/src/main.rs#L10).\r\n",
